USDA Declares Meat Products Unfit Federal food inspectors declared unfit for human consumption 21 million pounds of meat and poultry produced by the same Arkansas plant from which 30 million pounds of meat products were recalled three months ago.
The plant on Dec. 22 recalled 15 million pounds of hot dogs and the largest meat recall because of suspected contamination with a rare strain of the bacteria Listeria monocytogenes.
